  "text": "We take a well chosen sequence of trees (B ∆,n ) with maximum degree ∆, for which every tree of maximum degree ∆ is a subgraph of an element of the sequence, and the elements of the sequence contains the previous element as a subtree. By Lemma 2.5, it is enough to prove that d(B ∆,n ) tends to (1 − ). For this purpose, we define the so-called Bethe-trees recursively, as follows [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . Definition 3.14. The tree B ∆,1 is a single vertex. The tree B ∆,n consists of a vertex u which is joined by edges to the roots of each of ∆ − 1 copies of B ∆,n−1 . The vertex u is the root of B ∆,n .",
